message.content: Most women in Austria have a generally accepting attitude towards divorce. They view it as a viable option to end an unhappy or dysfunctional marriage. Women in Austria prioritize their personal happiness and well-being, and they believe that divorce can provide them with the opportunity to start afresh and find a more fulfilling relationship. They also recognize that divorce can be a challenging process, especially when children are involved, but they are willing to navigate these difficulties in order to pursue a better future for themselves and their families.
